    "source": "_Overview_of_Melon_Varieties__Ripening__and_Health",
    "contenu": "Here is the structured content from the document titled \"A SURVEY OF COMMON FRUITS\":\n\n---\n\n### Digesting Enzymes and Melon Contamination\n- **Digesting Enzyme:** Cucumisin\n- **Prevention:** Prevents gelatin gels from setting unless the enzyme is denatured by cooking or an excess of gelatin is used.\n- **Contamination:** Melon surface can become contaminated with microbes in the field, causing food poisoning when these microbes are introduced into the flesh during cutting.\n- **Recommendation:** Wash melons thoroughly in hot soapy water before preparing them.\n\n### Melon Families and Qualities\n- **Western Melons:** Mostly fall into two families:\n  - **Summer Melons:** Highly aromatic and perishable, usually with rough rinds. Includes true cantaloupes and muskmelons.\n  - **Winter Melons:** Less aromatic and less perishable, with smooth or wrinkled rinds. Includes honeydews, casabas, and canaries.\n\n### Melon Ripening\n- **Vine-ripening:** Important for all melons as they don't store starch and become sweeter after harvest. A remnant of the stem on an aromatic melon indicates it was harvested before becoming fully ripe.\n- **Aroma Consistency:** The aroma of naturally ripened melons may differ off the vine and will not be the same as the aroma of vine-ripened melons.\n\n### Varieties of Melons\n\n#### Summer Melons\n- **Cantaloupe:** Smooth or lightly netted, orange flesh, rich flavor.\n- **Muskmelon:** Deeply netted, sometimes misnamed “cantaloupe” in the U.S.\n- **Galia, Ha Ogen, Rocky Ford:** Green flesh, sweet and aromatic.\n- **Ambrosia, Sierra Gold:** Orange flesh.\n- **Persian:** Large, orange, mild.\n- **Sharlyn/Ananas:** Translucent pale flesh.\n- **Pancha (charentais x muskmelon):** Netted and ribbed, orange, very aromatic.\n\n#### Winter Melons\n- **Honeydews:** Smooth rind, green or orange flesh, sweet, mild aroma.\n- **Casaba, Santa Claus:** Wrinkled or smooth rind, white flesh, less sweet or aromatic than honeydew.\n- **Canary:** Slightly wrinkled rind, white flesh, crisp, aromatic.\n\n### Hybrids\n- **Crenshaw (Persian x casaba):** Green-yellow wrinkled rind, orange flesh, juicy, aromatic."
  },
